<p>I love doing presentations and I&#39;m happy to say that we have a few for <a href="http://www.chris-granger.com/2012/04/12/light-table---a-new-ide-concept/">Light Table</a> lined up throughout the year:</p>

<ul>
<li>6/7/2012 - <a href="http://www.meetup.com/The-Bay-Area-Clojure-User-Group/events/47874162/">Bay Area Clojure Meetup</a></li>
<li>7/19/2012 - <a href="http://www.oscon.com/oscon2012/public/schedule/speaker/139366">OSCON</a></li>
<li>9/23/2012 - <a href="https://thestrangeloop.com/sessions/behind-the-mirror">Strange Loop</a></li>
<li>11/7/2012 - <a href="http://oredev.org/2012/sessions/behind-the-mirror--a-look-at-how-we-develop">Oredev</a></li>
</ul>

<p>The Clojure meetup will be a really informal demo of <a href="http://www.chris-granger.com/2012/04/12/light-table---a-new-ide-concept/">Light Table</a> with most of the time spent on Q&amp;A, while the others are more normal talks. I&#39;ll let you know if any more crop up!</p>
